<div id="about-the-trust">
    <div class="section">
        <div id="section-title">
            <h2 class="text-size--medium">About Us</h2>
        </div>
        <div id="section-content">

            <p class="text-size--small"><b>
                    The Bridges Community Trust began as “The Meadows Forum” in 1996, started by
                    local residents for local
                    residents to improve the area in which they lived and/or worked, to give the local community a voice
                    that would be heard and to improve the social and economic status of the area. The One Stop Shop was
                    established in July 1998 under the name The Meadows Partnership Trust. In 2017 the name was changed
                    to
                    The Bridges Community to reflect a broader area of service delivery, and in 2013, the Trust expanded
                    to
                    include Clifton.
                </b></p>

            <p class="text-size--small">
                We support local voluntary and community sector organisations, the Meadows Food Bank and local
                individuals.
                Since 2006 we have been delivering successful employment support both on a one-to-one basis and by
                provision
                of Work Clubs, that are open and accessible to all by appointment only. We deliver this service from the
                One
                Stop Shop and from outreach locations such as local libraries. We have held the MATRIX Quality Standard
                for
                Careers Information, Advice and Guidance continuously since 2006, with successful reaccreditation in
                September 2018.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
